A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Estates and Trusts – Registers of Wills – Salary
3 FOR the purpose of altering the maximum annual salary of a register of wills; repealing as
4 obsolete a certain minimum annual salary for the register of wills for Baltimore City;
5 and generally relating to the salary of a register of wills.
6 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
7 Article – Estates and Trusts
8 Section 2–205
9 Annotated Code of Maryland
10 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
11 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
12 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
13 Article – Estates and Trusts
14 2–205.
15 (a) (1) It is the intent of this section that each register shall receive a fair and
16 adequate compensation for the effort and duties required of the register by the register’s
17 office.
18 (2) The volume and character of work done by the register shall be in
19 comparison to the salary fixed by the Board of Public Works for each of the other registers.
20 (b) (1) Each register is entitled to receive an annual salary of not more than
21 [$146,500, to be determined in each instance by the Board of Public Works] THE SALARY
22 OF A STATE EMPLOYEE AT GRADE 26, STEP 20 OF THE STATE OF MARYLAND
